    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-20T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="273"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                    Armaments/11–2048: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>, in Paris,
                        to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-20T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 20, 1948—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 858. Re <gloss target="#t_Gadel1"
                        >Gadel</gloss> 542 November 19.<note n="1" xml:id="d273fn1">Telegram <gloss
                            target="#t_Gadel1">Gadel</gloss> 542 read as follows: “Dept like have
                        any comment other Dels and estimate <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>
                        on <gloss target="#t_CCA1">CCA</gloss> continuing present order plan work or
                        any deviation therefrom resulting from <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>
                        approved disarmament resolution and discussions leading to its adoption.”
                            (501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss> Armaments/11–1948)</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> and other delegations believe approved
                    disarmament resolution offers opportunity to place work of <gloss
                        target="#t_CCA1">CCA</gloss> on new and satisfactory basis. Urge
                    postponement inter-Departmental conferences and Department action until return
                        <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>, particularly Page Smith and Osborn
                    acquainted with latest discussions other delegations Paris.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
